<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="kind-n">kind <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kaɪnd/    美 /kaɪnd/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-sort-type">1.★ <strong>种类 (sort / type)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You can find <strong>all kinds of</strong> information in just a few minutes on the Internet. 
在互联网上，只要几分钟你就能找到各种各样的信息。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="a-kind-of">a kind of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>…的一种；有几分；稍稍：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>An e-mail is usually a kind of informal letter.
电子邮件通常是一种非正式信件。</p><footer>译林② – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had a kind of feeling that this might happen.
我当时就隐约感觉到会出这事。</p></div>

<h3 id="kind-of">kind of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>有点儿；有几分</strong><br />
slightly; in some ways：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was kind of upset that you weren't there.
你没出现我有点不安。</p></div></div>